headline: Insurance Stocks Gain Ground in Turbulent Markets. Boring Might Be the Way to Go.
summary: Insurance stocks are quietly outperforming, delivering steady gains as volatility rattles much of the broader market.  Through Thursday’s close, the stock is up 6% for the week, achieving its heaviest weekly volume in the past 10 months without even counting Friday’s session.

headline: Is It Too Late To Consider Chubb (CB) After A Strong Multi‑Year Share Price Run?
summary: If you are wondering whether Chubb's current share price still offers value or if most of the opportunity is already reflected, this article will help you make sense of what the market may be pricing in. Chubb's shares most recently closed at US$331.28, with returns of 8.2% over 7 days, 7.1% over 30 days, 6.8% year to date, 23.0% over 1 year, 62.1% over 3 years and 115.8% over 5 years. headline: President Trump's tariffs fueled U.S. Customs bond market boom. Now billions hang on Supreme Court ruling
summary: Companies are anxious for Supreme Court ruling on Trump tariffs, but in addition to trade tax refunds, billions were paid in customs bonds and collateral.
